guide.entry.intro.page.0=This is the test page for the Practical Guide of Practical Things. It is designed to give you the practical knowledge to use all of the practical constructs in this mod.\n\nAll of the information in this guide is located in the language file, including recipes and all other information. §oNone§r of it is in the code.\n\nIt is based on §oEntries§r, each entry can have many pages, and each page can be of one type. Though at this point only text and recipes are implemented. A page is defined with at least two* lines in the lang file.§a§o\n\nguide.entry.ENTRYNAME.PAGENUM.type=TYPE\nguide.entry.ENTRYNAME.PAGENUM=CONTENT\n\n§r§0The type line can be either §otext§r or §orecipe§r, though if it doesn't exist it will default to §otext§r. These formats will be discussed in further detail later.\n\nThe guide book will search forward from page 0->∞ for a plain §a§o...PAGENUM=SOMETHING§r§0 line to determine the length of the guide, stopping once it finds one missing.\n\n\n\n*no type line is required for text

